organic_results.title: Education as a dimension of status incongruence between parents and the self perceptions of college students
organic_results.snippet: This study focuses on black students from families in which wives have or have not, attained higher educational statuses than husbands. On one dimension of self-perception--rejection of self-derogatory images--students who had come from families in which the mother's level of educational attainment was higher than that of the father's evaluated themselves significantly higher than other students. Other relationships involving internal control, drop-out rate, acceptance of the Protestant ethic, and, to some extent, a positive self-evaluation …
